            And therefore, I must craue your Christian patience, that I may clere the former doctrines, from the two former imputations; especially, from that imputation of falsehood: which is the greatest infamie, if it be true, and the greatest iniurie, if it be false, that can possibly be cast vpon a Preacher: yea a farre greater iniurie, then to call him either a murderer, a theife, or a traitor. For to be a false teacher, is to be all these together; it is to be both a murdererer of mens soules; a theefe, vnto Christs fold: and a trator to Gods honour. And therefore, Saint Hierom saith, that Neminem decet in suspicione baereseos esse patientem.
