               selues. The Apostle Paul compareth Faith and Hope,1. Cor. 13.13. and Charity together, and he preferreth Charity before both the other: shall we therefore affirme, that he disgraceth both Faith and Hope? or that he maketh either of them vnnecessarie for a Christian? God forbid. To come a little neerer vnto our owne question: The Apostle Iames biddeth vs, that If any man lacke wisedome, hee shll aske it of God.
               
Whereby he implieth that spirituall wisedome may be attained by prayings.Iam. 1.5. Shall we therefore say that S. Iames disableth Preaching, &amp; maketh it vnnecessary to the attaining of wisedom? Nay, (to come home vnto the ve
